  • Method Details

    • multiplyMatrix

      public void multiplyMatrix​(Matrix other)
      Multiplies matrix by another one

      The function is executed only if both matrices can be multiplied For example : If you try to multiply these 2 matrices, you will get a new one : { 7 , 3 , 2 } { 1 , 1 , 3 } { 19 , 26 , 35 } { 5 , 9 , 2 } x { 2 , 5 , 2 } = { 29 , 54 , 41 } { 0 , 0 , 1 } { 3 , 2 , 4 } { 3 , 2 , 4 } If you try to multiply these 2 matrices, you will get an error, and get back the actual matrix { 7 , 3 } { 1 , 1 } { 7 , 3 } { 5 , 9 } x { 2 , 5 } = { 5 , 9 } { 0 , 0 } { 3 , 2 } { 0 , 0 }

      Parameters:
      other - the other matrix

    • sumMatrix

      public void sumMatrix​(Matrix other)
      Sums matrix by another one

      The function is executed only if both matrices can be summed For example : If you try to sum these 2 matrices, you will get a new one : { 7 , 3 , 2 } { 1 , 1 , 3 } { 8 , 4 , 5 } { 5 , 9 , 2 } + { 2 , 5 , 2 } = { 7 , 14 , 4 } { 0 , 0 , 1 } { 3 , 2 , 4 } { 3 , 2 , 5 } If you try to sums these 2 matrices, you will get an error, and get back the actual matrix { 7 , 3 } { 1 , 1 } { 7 , 3 } { 5 , 9 } + { 2 , 5 } = { 5 , 9 } { 0 , 0 } { 3 , 2 } { 0 , 0 }

      Parameters:
      other - the other matrix

    • subMatrix

      public void subMatrix​(Matrix other)
      Subtracts matrix by another one

      The function is executed only if both matrices can be subtracted For example : If you try to subtract these 2 matrices, you will get a new one : { 7 , 3 , 2 } { 1 , 1 , 3 } { 6 , 2 , -1 } { 5 , 9 , 2 } - { 2 , 5 , 2 } = { 3 , 4 , 0 } { 0 , 0 , 1 } { 3 , 2 , 4 } { -3 , -2 , -3 } If you try to subtract these 2 matrices, you will get an error, and get back the actual matrix { 7 , 3 } { 1 , 1 } { 7 , 3 } { 5 , 9 } - { 2 , 5 } = { 5 , 9 } { 0 , 0 } { 3 , 2 } { 0 , 0 }

      Parameters:
      other - the other matrix
